records.addlTxt: Case Called: 2:33pm. Clerk: Denise. INCLUDES 15CF196, 15CM235. State appears by ADA Lisa Gramer. Deft appears in custody and by Atty Robin Kennedy. Matter set for Prelim and Plea/Sentencing. State recites history of the matter.  *VRCW. State recites history of matter and Victim Rights. *VRCW. Crt proceeds with Waiver of Prelim. Waiver of Prelim. filed.  Court questions deft as to waiver. Court finds waiver freely and voluntarily made. COURT finds PC - Defendant bound over for arraignment & trial.  Information filed.  Reading Waived. Crt proceeds with Plea.  Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights & Counsel filed.  State moves to amend ct 1 (contribute/delinquency child (death) to 1 ct of (intentionally contributing delinquency of child (which act contributed to would be a felony)- class H felony) (948.40(1) & (4)(b) - crt grants. State moves to DRI 15CM235- crt grants. PLEA: NO CONTEST - amend ct 1 (intentionally contributing delinquency of child (which act contributed to would be a felony)- class H felony).  Crt advises def of rights & penalties & ques def to understanding.  Crt finds plea & waiver freely & vol made, a factual basis & def guilty .  Statements by State, Defense and Defendant. COURT ORDERS: SWH - 3 yrs probation. CONDITONS: Impose & Stay 1 yr jail for rule violations; 45 days credit; Enroll & Complete Corrective Thinking; Counseling; No driving w/out valid dl; Must obtain valid dl w/in probation time; No dangerous weapons; No contact with victim(s):  A.C.D. (DOB: 2/16/01), D.C.O. (DOB: 1/11/01), D.J.E. (DOB: 4/18/01), J.P. (DOB: 6/23/01), E.J.S. (DOB:  7/08/03), J.K. (DOB: 10/20/98), T.D.W. (DOB: 4/14/00), J.A.T. (DOB:  6/1/01), D.Y; and known gang members; Court Costs; DNA Sample & Surcharge; Perform 300 hrs Community Service at the rate of 100 hrs per year; if determined to be appropriate that Defendant to do something appropriate due to victims family.  Crt advises and defendant signs Ineligible Voting Form. Defense provides defendant's statement to the Court- State may provide ltr to victim's family. Adjourned: 3:06pm.
Waiver of Prelim on April 16, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
Status conference on April 7, 2015 at 09:30 am.
